 int getCurrentMessageCasualTime()
          Get current messages casual time
A message casual time is a sum of successive messages that has been caused by another message.
Example
msgA -> msgB -> msgC -> msgE
        msgB -> msgD -> msgF -> msgG

sendToOthers

public final void sendToOthers(boolean message)
Send a message to all out going ports, except a port that it just received. NOTE: This will work only for Bidirectional link. For uni-directional link, it will work only if a label of incoming port is the same as out going port label. Otherwise, all out going ports will be sent.

Specified by:
sendToOthers in interface IMessagePassingModel
Parameters:
message - A message that need to be sent

Send a message to all out going ports except a port that it received latest. NOTE: This will work only for Bidirectional link. For uni-directional link, it will work only if a label of incoming port is the same as out going port label. Otherwise, all out going ports will be sent.

Specified by:
sendToOthers in interface IMessagePassingModel
Parameters:
message - A message that need to be sent

getCurrentMessageCasualTime

public final int getCurrentMessageCasualTime()
Get current messages casual time
A message casual time is a sum of successive messages that has been caused by another message.
Example
msgA -> msgB -> msgC -> msgE
        msgB -> msgD -> msgF -> msgG

In this example msgA causes the creation of msgB, and msgB causes the creation of msgC and msgD, and msgD cause msgF and so on, while msgE has no cause to creation of any message.

The current message casual time when msgG is created is 4 because there are 4 hops from msgA to msgG from this illustration

Returns:
a message casual time which start from the beginning of the process to a current call of this method
